news.title: Lucknow development body to develop Udyog Nagar, Naimish Nagar
news.para: Singh said that Udyog Nagar will be developed over 5,610 acres in Sadar and Sarojininagar tehsils. Land was identified in villages, including Bhaliya, Adampur Indwara, Behru, Jaliamau, Madarpur and Ibrahimganj.

news.title: Centre set to push amendments to DDA, to give fillip to land pooling policy
news.para: The Centre is planning to push amendments to the Delhi Development Act which will make land pooling mandatory for all residents if a certain percentage -- 70% -- of owners of land in an area agree to pool land.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh to launch three-month drive to regularise or raze unauthorised constructions
news.para: During a review of the housing development authorities, it was found that out of the 2.50 lakh complaints pertaining to unauthorised and illegal construction activity forwarded to authorities during the 2024-25 financial year, only 3,507 have been disposed of, while the remaining ones remain pending.

news.title: Lucknow: Lottery for Anant Nagar Scheme plots on June 10
news.para: District magistrate Vishakh G recently inspected the site and reviewed development progress. He directed the officials to widen the connecting road between the scheme and UPSIDA as well as Kisan Path.

news.title: Prayagraj development body offers 764 flats for sale
news.para: The flats cater to various categories, including EWS, LIG, 1BHK, 2BHK, and 3BHK, and will be allocated through a lottery system, providing a fair opportunity to prospective buyers.

news.title: Developers get Gujarat RERA notices for pre-registration bookings
news.para: Sources said that GujRERA is going to start a mega campaign against this practice across the state. The authority also announced new rules for the marketing of projects, which will come into effect from June 15.

news.title: Builders in a fix as 327 building plans await Ranchi civic body's approval since January 2025
news.para: A legal officer is a key official required for the final approval of the plans. Even though an officer was appointed earlier this month following a directive of Jharkhand High Court, the approvals remain pending.

news.title: Experts estimate free sale portion in Dharavi at 140 million sq ft
news.para: Total rehab cost including housing units for eligible beneficiaries and other for affordable rental housing is projected at Rs 95,790 crore, of which construction cost will be Rs 23,800 crore.

news.title: Complainant cannot move RERA, consumer court at same time: WBREAT
news.para: ​"Since the cause of action in the proceedings before a Consumer Commission is identical with that of the Regulatory Authority, the complainant has to elect either of the two proceedings and cannot proceed with both simultaneously," WBREAT chairperson ruled.

news.title: Zara's founder buys office building in Barcelona for $283 million: Sources
news.para: Blackstone sold the 28,000-square-metre building on Avenida Diagonal, currently rented by the Spanish editorial business Planeta, to Ortega's investment vehicle Pontegadea, the sources said.

news.title: UP-RERA streamlining process of projects registration, dispute resolutions of homebuyers
news.para: Bhoosreddy said the property market in the state has been growing with the application of registration of projects coming from many districts in the states.

news.title: BL Kashyap & Sons posts net loss of ₹3.28 crore in Q4 FY25
news.para: BL Kashyap & Sons' net consolidated total income stood at ₹297.35 crore in Q4 FY25, a dip of 14.75 per cent from ₹348.78 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Puravankara's net loss widens to ₹88 crore in Q4 FY25
news.para: Puravankara's net consolidated total income stood at ₹563.70 crore in Q4 FY25, a dip of 40.47 per cent from ₹946.84 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Whiteland Corporation invests ₹5,600 crore in Westin Residences Gurugram
news.para: The project will span across 7.78 hectares (approximately 20 acres), with 1,700 three-bedroom and four-bedroom residences ranging from 248 to 402 sq meters (approximately 2,673 to 4,328 sq ft).

news.title: Embassy Developments posts ₹123.04 crore profit in Q4 FY25
news.para: Embassy Developments' net consolidated total income stood at ₹1,182.61 crore in Q4 FY25 as against ₹401.54 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Asian Granito India posts ₹16.41 crore profit in Q4 FY25
news.para: Asian Granito India's net consolidated total income stood at ₹478.49 crore in Q4 FY25, a growth of 11.78 per cent from ₹428.06 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Shapoorji Pallonji Group secures $3.4 billion in private credit deal
news.para: About a dozen large investors - some using multiple funds - bought zero-coupon rupee bonds that offer a yield of 19.75%, the people said, asking not to be identified because the information is private. The debt matures in three years.

news.title: Residents of BDD chawls in Worli will get homes before July: Maharashtra minister
news.para: Shelar, a senior BJP MLA and guardian minister of Mumbai's suburban district, made the announcement while inspecting the progress of the redevelopment towers being constructed under the first phase of the Worli BDD Chawl Redevelopment Project.
